@epa-wg/trang-native
====================

This package distributes a native (GraalVM-compiled) build of Trang, a
RELAX NG / DTD / XSD schema converter originally authored by
James Clark and currently maintained by the relaxng community at
https://github.com/relaxng/jing-trang.

Upstream Trang source is licensed under the 2-clause BSD license; the
full text is in LICENSE. This package's wrapper scripts (under
scripts/, src/, bin/trang.mjs) are also released under the 2-clause
BSD license to keep the distribution license-uniform.

Each released binary is built by GitHub Actions from a pinned upstream
revision recorded in upstream.json. The build provenance — runner OS,
runner arch, GraalVM version, jing-trang commit SHA — is stamped into
the release notes and into the per-archive metadata.json sidecar.

Trang itself does not bundle a JRE in the GraalVM native-image build;
no Java runtime is required on consumer machines.
